Package org.net4care.forwarder

This package contains classes that specifically are used on the home device side.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    DataUploader
    An instance of DataUploader is responsible for forwarding/sending/uploading a StandardTeleObservation instance from the home device to the Net4Care server side.
    FutureResult
    The result of an asynchronous upload.
    FutureResultWithAnswer
    A Future value that also upon completion has a returned string value from the server.
    Query
    Any query for a set of observations must implement this interface.
    QueryResult
    Encapsulate the actual result of a successful query for a set of observations to the server.
    ServerConnector
    An instance of ServerConnector is responsible for the actual upload of the on-the-wire formatted string of the observation to the Net4Care server side.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    Query.QueryResponseType
    Define the type of the returned observations from a query, either STO's or PHMR's.

Package org.net4care.forwarder Description

This package contains classes that specifically are used on the home device side.

Most of the interfaces are not relevant for an application developer making a home telemedical application. Application developers should just create an instance of the StandardDataUploader from package forwarder.delegate.
